.Dd March 30, 2026
.Dt PAX 1
.Os Kayoko
.Sh NAME
.Nm pax ,
.Nm tar ,
.Nm cpio
.Nd portable archive interchange and multicall archiving utility
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm pax
.Op Fl rwv
.Op Fl f Ar archive
.Op Fl x Ar format
.Op Ar pattern ...
.Nm tar
.Op Fl cvf Ar archive
.Op Ar file ...
.Nm cpio
.Fl o | i
.Op Fl v
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility shall list, read, or write archive files, or copy directory
hierarchies.
.Pp
When invoked as
.Nm tar
or
.Nm cpio
via symbolic links, the utility provides a simplified interface compatible with
those traditional archivers.
.Pp
The following options are supported for
.Nm pax :
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl r
Read an archive file. If
.Fl w
is also specified, enter copy mode.
.It Fl w
Write files to an archive.
.It Fl v
Verbose mode. List filenames as they are processed.
.It Fl f Ar archive
Specify the pathname of the input or output archive. If not specified,
standard input or output is used.
.It Fl x Ar format
Specify the output archive format. The formats supported are
.Sy ustar
(default POSIX tar) and
.Sy cpio
(SVR4 new ASCII).
.El
.Sh OPERANDS
The
.Nm pax
utility supports four modes of operation:
.Bl -bullet
.It
.Sy List :
Neither
.Fl r
nor
.Fl w
are specified.
.It
.Sy Read :
.Fl r
is specified, but
.Fl w
is not.
.It
.Sy Write :
.Fl w
is specified, but
.Fl r
is not.
.It
.Sy Copy :
Both
.Fl r
and
.Fl w
are specified.
.El
.Sh COMPATIBILITY
When invoked as
.Nm tar :
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl c
Create a new
.Sy ustar
format archive.
.It Fl x
Extract from an archive (default behavior if -c is absent).
.El
.Pp
When invoked as
.Nm cpio :
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl o
Output mode. Read a list of pathnames from standard input and create a
.Sy cpio
format archive.
.It Fl i
Input mode. Extract files from a
.Sy cpio
archive provided on standard input.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr cpio 1 ,
.Xr tar 1 ,
.Xr zlib 3
